result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob A Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jacob A Rodriguez is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jacob A Rodriguez was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property - Domestic Abuse Repeater [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Domestic Abuse Repeater], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Jacob A Rodriguez was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct - Domestic Abuse Repeater [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Repeater, Domestic Abuse], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jacob A Rodriguez in court with attorney Richard L Voss.  Defendant Jacob A Rodriguez in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT #2, dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.
  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered dismissal of the Criminal Habituality Enhancer (939.62(1)(a), on both Counts #1 and #4. 

 AS TO COUNT #1 and COUNT #4: (without Criminal Habituality Enhancer),  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.  Courts finds that State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

 AS TO COUNT #1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS (CONSECUTIVE to count #4 and any other sentence), with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 

 AS TO COUNT #4: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS, (CONSECUTIVE to count #1 and any other sentence), with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 4 YEARS with the following conditions (as to counts #1 and #4).:  
* Court ordered the defendant to serve 60 DAYS
   in the House of Correction.  Stayed pending review.
* Successfully complete "Batterers intervention"
   counseling and continue programming.
* Attend and complete parenting classes.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
   and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol.
* Successfully complete any other counseling and/or
   treatment deemed appropriate.
* No violent contact with the victim, Dana R.  
  Defendant may not reside in the home until BIP 
  is stared and successful and agent approves.   
* Defendant must not have any alcohol 
   in prescence of children, but victim may supervise.
* Obtain and maintain employment.
* No firearms; weapons.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence
   surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by
   the Department of Corrections, during period of probation 
   or CIVIL JUDGMENT to issue.
* Restitution is set at zero.
**PROBATION REVIEW HEARING TO BE REQUESTED BY AGENT.  
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
